1
00:00:00,003 --> 00:00:32,003
( Watch on www.kissasia.co, .club, .be, .org, .net, .id, .xyz )

2
00:00:31,997 --> 00:00:33,777
Did you stay up late last night?

3
00:00:34,760 --> 00:00:35,240
Yeah.

4
00:00:37,400 --> 00:00:40,110
Hey, don’t fall asleep yet. Tell me the route first.

5
00:00:51,520 --> 00:00:52,690
Whose car did you take?

6
00:00:53,930 --> 00:00:57,640
Well, you said there wasn’t a car to move your stuff, so I asked P’Johan.

7
00:00:58,940 --> 00:01:00,510
He gave me the keys to this one.

8
00:01:03,910 --> 00:01:05,200
Hope he's just renting it.

9
00:01:14,500 --> 00:01:16,230
Turn right at the intersection.

10
00:01:17,450 --> 00:01:18,260
Got it.

11
00:01:19,730 --> 00:01:21,070
We’re here, we’re here.

12
00:03:10,640 --> 00:03:12,270
Ter, Maew.

13
00:03:12,800 --> 00:03:13,520
We’re here.

14
00:03:13,660 --> 00:03:14,940
Ow, Daotok.

15
00:03:15,180 --> 00:03:16,450
How’s they gonna wake up if you just call them like that?

16
00:03:16,950 --> 00:03:18,240
You get out. I’ll handle it.

17
00:03:20,620 --> 00:03:22,160
Ter, Maew.

18
00:03:22,580 --> 00:03:23,120
Wake up.

19
00:03:27,020 --> 00:03:28,040
Wake up.

20
00:03:29,350 --> 00:03:31,190
Ouch.

21
00:03:38,620 --> 00:03:39,240
We’re here.

22
00:03:39,520 --> 00:03:42,510
North, why are you yelling?

23
00:03:42,820 --> 00:03:44,810
You could’ve just called us nicely.

24
00:04:21,000 --> 00:04:21,900
Come on, let’s move the stuff.

25
00:04:22,310 --> 00:04:22,860
Yeah.

26
00:04:45,790 --> 00:04:46,830
Which floor is it?

27
00:04:48,080 --> 00:04:49,090
The 7th floor.

28
00:04:49,820 --> 00:04:50,520
Shit.

29
00:04:51,360 --> 00:04:54,550
Your new condo is so fancy. You’re rich, Daotok.

30
00:04:55,540 --> 00:04:56,160
I’m not rich.

31
00:04:57,000 --> 00:04:58,090
They gave me a discount.

32
00:04:58,450 --> 00:05:00,410
Really? How much?

33
00:05:01,410 --> 00:05:02,330
70%.

34
00:05:02,570 --> 00:05:03,340
What?!

35
00:05:05,250 --> 00:05:06,910
Why is it discounted that much?

36
00:05:07,390 --> 00:05:10,210
With that kind of discount, is there some kind of promotion or what?

37
00:05:11,110 --> 00:05:11,960
Like…

38
00:05:12,130 --> 00:05:14,120
comes with a couple of ghosts or something?

39
00:05:14,850 --> 00:05:17,280
- Hey!
- Watch your mouth, North.

40
00:05:17,910 --> 00:05:19,720
Doesn’t it make you suspicious at all?

41
00:05:20,090 --> 00:05:21,770
With that kind of discount, they might as well let you stay for free.

42
00:05:22,225 --> 00:05:22,980
Right?

43
00:05:27,600 --> 00:05:28,990
Hey! That scared me.

44
00:05:29,274 --> 00:05:32,460
- Maybe it’s a power flicker.
- See? I told you it probably comes with something.

45
00:05:36,990 --> 00:05:38,400
The light’s broken.

46
00:05:39,450 --> 00:05:40,860
Let me introduce myself.

47
00:05:41,420 --> 00:05:42,430
My name is P’Pae.

48
00:05:42,650 --> 00:05:43,830
I’m the owner of this condo.

49
00:05:44,340 --> 00:05:47,100
If you rent a room here, I’ll give you a 50% discount.

50
00:05:48,270 --> 00:05:49,930
But if you rent room…

51
00:05:51,610 --> 00:05:52,650
702,

52
00:05:53,550 --> 00:05:54,790
I’ll give you 70% off.

53
00:06:01,820 --> 00:06:03,260
Are pets allowed here?

54
00:06:04,280 --> 00:06:05,190
Of course.

55
00:06:05,500 --> 00:06:06,670
What kind of pet are you keeping?

56
00:06:07,370 --> 00:06:08,910
Someone once kept a snake here.

57
00:06:10,110 --> 00:06:12,900
You could even keep a buffalo if you want.

58
00:06:13,090 --> 00:06:13,890
I mean it.

59
00:06:19,910 --> 00:06:20,680
Okay.

60
00:06:21,290 --> 00:06:23,350
Then I’ll take room 702.

61
00:06:24,210 --> 00:06:27,800
You really want to rent room 702?

62
00:06:29,660 --> 00:06:30,780
Yes.

63
00:06:35,748 --> 00:06:37,420
- Is something wrong?
- No.

64
00:06:38,000 --> 00:06:41,400
Nothing at all. Here’s the contract.

65
00:06:42,330 --> 00:06:45,150
The rental contract. 70% discount.

66
00:06:45,620 --> 00:06:46,850
Please read it.

67
00:06:50,580 --> 00:06:51,600
70%.

68
00:06:52,805 --> 00:06:54,510
I have a special ability.

69
00:06:59,608 --> 00:07:00,666
Excuse me.

70
00:07:05,510 --> 00:07:06,480
Sorry.

71
00:07:06,850 --> 00:07:08,480
Hey, let’s go eat shabu.

72
00:07:11,120 --> 00:07:13,590
Feel… happy.

73
00:07:17,750 --> 00:07:20,480
I can sense people’s feelings.

74
00:07:36,070 --> 00:07:38,200
Your life is about to take a turn.

75
00:07:38,840 --> 00:07:42,330
Wait, am I gonna win the lottery?

76
00:07:42,380 --> 00:07:43,730
- Ouch.
- No, North.

77
00:07:44,470 --> 00:07:46,910
Not a life-changing turn.

78
00:07:47,020 --> 00:07:49,710
- Huh?
- But it might affect some parts of your life.

79
00:07:50,010 --> 00:07:51,230
Now I’m stressed.

80
00:07:51,860 --> 00:07:53,310
I’m not watching anymore then.

81
00:07:55,160 --> 00:07:57,140
I can read people’s fortunes.

82
00:08:03,790 --> 00:08:04,640
And…

83
00:08:09,930 --> 00:08:11,910
I can communicate with spirits.

84
00:08:12,300 --> 00:08:13,340
It was just a power flicker, right?

85
00:08:14,650 --> 00:08:15,630
It’s nothing.

86
00:08:16,780 --> 00:08:17,820
Really?

87
00:08:19,010 --> 00:08:20,000
You’re bold for saying that.

88
00:08:37,445 --> 00:08:38,317
This is the room.

89
00:08:45,600 --> 00:08:46,960
Why did you bring so much stuff?

90
00:08:47,075 --> 00:08:48,192
Thanks, Maew.

91
00:08:54,820 --> 00:08:55,700
Hey, Dao.

92
00:08:56,220 --> 00:08:59,030
Why does this floor feel so quiet?

93
00:08:59,670 --> 00:09:00,570
Umm.

94
00:09:01,100 --> 00:09:04,740
It’s just me and the room next door on this floor.

95
00:09:06,690 --> 00:09:09,150
Why? Is the rent that expensive?

96
00:09:27,640 --> 00:09:28,630
What’s wrong?

97
00:09:31,360 --> 00:09:36,250
Oh, nothing. It just feels… strange.

98
00:09:38,070 --> 00:09:39,130
- Ter.
- Hmm?

99
00:09:39,260 --> 00:09:40,260
My hand is freezing.

100
00:09:41,630 --> 00:09:42,210
Touch it.

101
00:09:43,300 --> 00:09:44,320
Shit.

102
00:09:44,700 --> 00:09:46,100
Look, I’ve got goosebumps.

103
00:09:47,585 --> 00:09:48,477
I don’t think this is normal.

104
00:09:50,870 --> 00:09:52,170
I’ve got a bad feeling about this room.

105
00:09:52,520 --> 00:09:53,620
It feels weird.

106
00:09:53,690 --> 00:09:54,990
So depressing.

107
00:09:56,620 --> 00:09:58,780
It’s just that no one’s lived here for a long time.

108
00:09:58,950 --> 00:10:00,770
That’s why it’s been closed up.

109
00:10:01,460 --> 00:10:02,330
It’s nothing.

110
00:10:07,010 --> 00:10:08,460
- Let’s move the stuff.
- Yeah, yeah.

111
00:10:08,930 --> 00:10:09,660
Hurry up.

112
00:10:33,710 --> 00:10:36,910
Thanks for helping me move.

113
00:10:37,830 --> 00:10:38,920
Sorry for the trouble.

114
00:10:40,670 --> 00:10:41,830
It’s fine, Dao.

115
00:10:42,590 --> 00:10:45,840
This is the first time you’ve ever asked us for help.

116
00:10:46,090 --> 00:10:47,520
We’re more than happy to.

117
00:10:48,980 --> 00:10:50,750
Did anyone even ask me?

118
00:10:51,230 --> 00:10:53,470
You’re happy to help too, right, North?

119
00:10:54,530 --> 00:10:55,650
Yeah, yeah, I’m happy.

120
00:10:55,940 --> 00:10:59,470
But can you treat us to some Moo Jum at least?

121
00:11:00,430 --> 00:11:01,110
Sure.

122
00:11:02,170 --> 00:11:03,900
Alright, we’ll head back first.

123
00:11:04,250 --> 00:11:06,090
If you need anything, just tell us.

124
00:11:06,460 --> 00:11:07,020
Mm.

125
00:11:08,068 --> 00:11:08,728
Thanks.

126
00:11:09,194 --> 00:11:09,688
See you.

127
00:11:11,020 --> 00:11:11,820
See you.

128
00:11:12,470 --> 00:11:13,110
Bye-bye.

129
00:11:14,951 --> 00:11:16,266
Bye, Dao.

130
00:11:42,460 --> 00:11:43,570
- Hey.
- Hey.

131
00:11:44,980 --> 00:11:45,700
What?

132
00:11:46,510 --> 00:11:48,920
Do you think Dao will be okay?

133
00:11:49,370 --> 00:11:50,320
Okay how?

134
00:11:53,260 --> 00:11:53,750
North.

135
00:11:55,080 --> 00:11:56,590
Haven’t you heard the news?

136
00:11:57,580 --> 00:11:58,700
What news?

137
00:12:02,940 --> 00:12:06,970
That condo has a history of a lot of deaths.

138
00:12:08,562 --> 00:12:11,200
Especially room 702.

139
00:12:11,310 --> 00:12:12,090
Hey.

140
00:12:12,600 --> 00:12:14,540
They say it’s a cursed room.

141
00:12:17,440 --> 00:12:18,210
Shit.

142
00:12:18,800 --> 00:12:20,460
Wait, I remember now.

143
00:12:20,750 --> 00:12:21,870
Pull over for a sec.

144
00:12:28,310 --> 00:12:28,950
Phoon.

145
00:12:30,210 --> 00:12:31,020
Tell us.

146
00:12:31,656 --> 00:12:32,800
Didn’t you read the news?

147
00:12:35,440 --> 00:12:36,250
Five years ago,

148
00:12:37,750 --> 00:12:40,320
a fourth-year medical student

149
00:12:40,780 --> 00:12:41,790
killed herself.

150
00:12:54,960 --> 00:12:59,880
They said she was stressed about school and her boyfriend.

151
00:13:00,490 --> 00:13:01,760
So she…

152
00:13:03,490 --> 00:13:04,590
jumped off the balcony.

153
00:13:09,350 --> 00:13:10,960
Then two years later,

154
00:13:11,340 --> 00:13:12,300
there was

155
00:13:13,340 --> 00:13:14,910
a working woman

156
00:13:15,980 --> 00:13:18,560
who was killed by her boyfriend in the bathroom.

157
00:13:18,780 --> 00:13:19,450
Hey.

158
00:13:27,580 --> 00:13:28,930
They said

159
00:13:29,650 --> 00:13:33,080
her throat was slit in the bathtub.

160
00:13:48,860 --> 00:13:50,090
Let’s talk this out.

161
00:13:50,810 --> 00:13:53,540
I’m the one paying the rent for this room.

162
00:13:54,030 --> 00:13:57,110
So that makes me the owner.

163
00:13:57,610 --> 00:13:59,230
You can check the contract.

164
00:14:00,140 --> 00:14:03,200
So anyone who has no right to be in this room

165
00:14:03,660 --> 00:14:07,710
please leave if possible.

166
00:14:16,400 --> 00:14:17,980
Hey.

167
00:14:18,720 --> 00:14:19,960
That’s already two bodies.

168
00:14:21,310 --> 00:14:22,410
And there’s a recent one too.

169
00:14:28,050 --> 00:14:30,170
A male student from the Faculty of Political Science

170
00:14:31,720 --> 00:14:36,260
was stabbed to death by his girlfriend while he was sleeping.

171
00:15:05,354 --> 00:15:08,130
I think he probably died without even knowing.

172
00:15:09,377 --> 00:15:09,934
Died.

173
00:15:12,068 --> 00:15:13,510
Was it last month?

174
00:15:15,110 --> 00:15:18,620
Oh right, I remember. It was on the university news.

175
00:15:18,720 --> 00:15:20,790
His girlfriend got arrested too, right?

176
00:15:21,770 --> 00:15:25,100
Guys, I think we should go back and get Daotok. This is dangerous.

177
00:15:25,500 --> 00:15:27,590
Really dangerous.

178
00:15:28,930 --> 00:15:30,520
Don’t panic yet.

179
00:15:30,990 --> 00:15:32,260
I think

180
00:15:33,650 --> 00:15:35,100
Dao already knows.

181
00:15:35,220 --> 00:15:38,790
About moving in there. What can we do?

182
00:15:38,940 --> 00:15:41,290
- You know him well, don’t you?
- Yeah, I do.

183
00:15:42,010 --> 00:15:45,710
I know he doesn’t like being forced. And I also know he’s not afraid of ghosts.

184
00:15:46,060 --> 00:15:49,230
- Because he can see ghosts.
- Yeah.

185
00:15:51,550 --> 00:15:54,900
No wonder no one lives on that floor. Just the room next to his.

186
00:15:55,390 --> 00:15:56,360
Damn.

187
00:15:57,320 --> 00:15:58,260
- Hey.
- Ah!

188
00:15:58,730 --> 00:16:00,960
Why are you grabbing me right now, Phoon?

189
00:16:01,010 --> 00:16:02,680
I was just saying we should hurry back.

190
00:16:02,770 --> 00:16:04,360
Oh. Right.

191
00:16:04,970 --> 00:16:05,550
Let’s go.

192
00:16:13,160 --> 00:16:14,020
Arthit.

193
00:16:15,200 --> 00:16:16,360
Thit.

194
00:16:18,890 --> 00:16:19,820
Thit.

195
00:16:22,030 --> 00:16:23,880
You’ve gotta help me.

196
00:16:24,640 --> 00:16:27,010
The new guy who moved in isn’t scared of me at all.

197
00:16:32,200 --> 00:16:33,130
Arthit.

198
00:16:35,020 --> 00:16:37,050
You asshole, I told you to wake up.

199
00:16:37,170 --> 00:16:39,250
Thit.

200
00:16:39,300 --> 00:16:42,120
Shut up, asshole. I’m trying to sleep.

201
00:16:43,670 --> 00:16:44,360
Shit.

202
00:17:04,020 --> 00:17:04,760
Hmm.

203
00:17:05,360 --> 00:17:06,130
Damn it.

204
00:17:06,410 --> 00:17:07,330
Make it a bit smaller.

205
00:17:08,220 --> 00:17:09,300
Even smaller.

206
00:17:09,680 --> 00:17:11,240
If it’s any smaller, you won’t see it.

207
00:17:17,340 --> 00:17:18,730
What should I do?

208
00:17:19,880 --> 00:17:22,110
If I adjust it more, it won’t stand out anymore.

209
00:17:22,460 --> 00:17:24,600
Try changing the position.

210
00:17:25,060 --> 00:17:25,770
Hmm.

211
00:17:26,570 --> 00:17:28,150
That’s a good idea.

212
00:17:29,580 --> 00:17:31,170
- Michael
- What?

213
00:17:31,350 --> 00:17:33,010
The new room looks pretty spacious.

214
00:17:33,730 --> 00:17:35,630
But I don’t feel very good about it.

215
00:17:36,110 --> 00:17:37,630
My friends said the same thing.

216
00:17:38,130 --> 00:17:39,660
Are you still going to move, Michael?

217
00:17:40,280 --> 00:17:40,880
No.

218
00:17:49,070 --> 00:17:52,360
There have been three deaths in this room’s history.

219
00:17:55,210 --> 00:17:57,230
Maybe it’s a ghost from somewhere else.

220
00:17:57,680 --> 00:17:59,270
Try taking off your bracelet.

221
00:17:59,560 --> 00:18:00,360
Maybe you’ll see it.

222
00:18:04,780 --> 00:18:05,490
No.

223
00:18:06,360 --> 00:18:07,290
I don’t want to see it.

224
00:18:28,700 --> 00:18:29,770
Stop knocking.

225
00:18:31,560 --> 00:18:32,290
Open up.

226
00:18:35,550 --> 00:18:36,330
I’m not opening it.

227
00:18:37,310 --> 00:18:38,590
And stop knocking.

228
00:18:42,860 --> 00:18:43,780
Are you lonely?

229
00:18:44,150 --> 00:18:45,380
Lonely my ass.

230
00:18:47,520 --> 00:18:48,610
Open the door!

231
00:18:51,940 --> 00:18:54,120
Why are you such a rude ghost?

232
00:18:54,940 --> 00:18:56,780
What ghost? I’m a person.

233
00:18:57,120 --> 00:18:58,500
I’m your neighbor next door.

234
00:19:03,930 --> 00:19:04,930
Open up.

235
00:19:05,580 --> 00:19:06,230
Hey!

236
00:19:08,640 --> 00:19:09,760
I said open it.

237
00:19:11,070 --> 00:19:13,560
Go tell Do to stop dragging the chair already.

238
00:19:13,960 --> 00:19:15,880
Damn it, I can’t sleep.

239
00:19:22,360 --> 00:19:23,380
P’Do didn’t do it.

240
00:19:27,190 --> 00:19:29,510
I don’t care. I’m blaming Do for now.

241
00:19:30,500 --> 00:19:31,150
Damn it.

242
00:19:31,230 --> 00:19:34,140
Whoever it is, tell them to stop making weird noises already.

243
00:19:34,180 --> 00:19:35,500
People are trying to sleep.

244
00:19:35,590 --> 00:19:36,790
Do you even know what time it is?

245
00:19:42,060 --> 00:19:43,060
Do you know about this?

246
00:19:45,320 --> 00:19:46,000
I’ll tell him.

247
00:19:48,040 --> 00:19:48,730
Yeah.

248
00:19:54,830 --> 00:19:55,790
Hey, Thit.

249
00:19:57,210 --> 00:19:59,350
When you wake up, come talk to me first.

250
00:19:59,910 --> 00:20:01,630
Can you see me? Hello?

251
00:20:09,630 --> 00:20:10,700
Can’t be helped.

252
00:20:11,410 --> 00:20:13,910
Why would a spirit from another room come here?

253
00:20:20,980 --> 00:20:22,010
What should we do?

254
00:20:27,380 --> 00:20:30,430
I probably can’t stop a spirit from killing itself over and over.

255
00:20:31,010 --> 00:20:34,470
But there should be a way to make the chair-dragging noise stop.

256
00:20:48,830 --> 00:20:51,750
From now on, could you not drag the chair so loudly, P’Earng?

257
00:20:53,530 --> 00:20:54,630
Will that even work?

258
00:20:55,030 --> 00:20:56,660
She’s a spirit from somewhere else.

259
00:20:57,930 --> 00:21:01,220
Not very powerful. Just wearing the bracelet makes her invisible.

260
00:21:01,570 --> 00:21:03,720
A spirit like this isn’t complicated.

261
00:21:13,310 --> 00:21:14,140
Thit.

262
00:21:14,720 --> 00:21:15,540
Thit.

263
00:21:18,980 --> 00:21:19,900
Arthit.

264
00:21:20,360 --> 00:21:24,510
Thit, Thit, Thit, Thit.

265
00:21:25,260 --> 00:21:27,090
Thit.

266
00:21:33,670 --> 00:21:35,110
Thit, Thit, Thit.

267
00:22:24,400 --> 00:22:25,320
You’re late again.

268
00:22:27,260 --> 00:22:28,630
You just got here too, asshole.

269
00:22:44,810 --> 00:22:45,680
Hey.

270
00:23:00,450 --> 00:23:01,230
You guys are late.

271
00:23:01,560 --> 00:23:02,480
I tried.

272
00:23:03,610 --> 00:23:04,630
Jo was late.

273
00:23:44,060 --> 00:23:46,670
So, you’ve moved into the new room?

274
00:23:46,850 --> 00:23:47,870
Yes, Papa.

275
00:23:49,060 --> 00:23:51,100
When will you bring Mr. John over?

276
00:23:51,830 --> 00:23:54,320
Um, I’m not free right now.

277
00:23:54,560 --> 00:23:55,860
Can it be next week?

278
00:23:58,260 --> 00:23:59,060
Sure.

279
00:23:59,420 --> 00:24:02,070
And the new room—nothing strange, right?

280
00:24:02,440 --> 00:24:04,050
I saw that it was cheap.

281
00:24:04,630 --> 00:24:06,360
So I'm a bit worried.

282
00:24:07,040 --> 00:24:09,340
Don’t overthink it, Papa.

283
00:24:10,320 --> 00:24:11,480
Let me talk to Dad.

284
00:24:12,490 --> 00:24:13,210
Sure, sure.

285
00:24:13,410 --> 00:24:15,030
Hey, your son wants to talk with you.

286
00:24:15,140 --> 00:24:15,770
Okay.

287
00:24:18,500 --> 00:24:20,270
Hey son. When you're coming home?

288
00:24:21,250 --> 00:24:22,260
I just got here.

289
00:24:22,770 --> 00:24:25,150
Can you snap a photo of Mr. John for me?

290
00:24:26,020 --> 00:24:27,450
Sure, I’ll send it to you.

291
00:24:27,980 --> 00:24:28,930
How’s your room?

292
00:24:30,630 --> 00:24:33,330
It’s so spacious and very convenient.

293
00:24:33,630 --> 00:24:34,590
Sounds good.

294
00:24:34,840 --> 00:24:35,840
See you soon.

295
00:24:36,190 --> 00:24:37,000
See you.

296
00:24:57,420 --> 00:24:58,900
Is that enough to fill you up?

297
00:25:00,850 --> 00:25:02,300
I’m not very hungry.

298
00:25:02,770 --> 00:25:05,460
You’re so stubborn, Michael. I’ll tell Ter next time.

299
00:25:06,550 --> 00:25:07,580
Don’t.

300
00:25:09,440 --> 00:25:10,520
What are you laughing at?

301
00:25:11,310 --> 00:25:17,580
When it’s the three of them—Ter, North, and Phoon—Michael always gives in every time.

302
00:25:18,160 --> 00:25:19,040
Mm.

303
00:25:20,390 --> 00:25:22,670
They’re my friends.

304
00:26:47,720 --> 00:26:48,920
That hurts.

305
00:26:49,320 --> 00:26:52,090
I’ll get mad if you keep hurting me like that.

306
00:26:54,550 --> 00:26:56,220
Give me your hand to hit.

307
00:27:00,010 --> 00:27:03,670
It hurts. Don’t do that to me.

308
00:27:05,830 --> 00:27:08,150
I can’t breathe.

309
00:27:08,750 --> 00:27:11,200
- I won’t do it.
- It hurts.

310
00:27:19,660 --> 00:27:20,620
Excuse me.

311
00:27:38,995 --> 00:27:40,260
Is something wrong?

312
00:27:42,310 --> 00:27:42,980
No.

313
00:27:47,260 --> 00:27:49,290
Good thing the door’s closed.

314
00:28:28,680 --> 00:28:29,730
What are you doing?

315
00:28:34,760 --> 00:28:35,840
Not talking.

316
00:28:38,070 --> 00:28:38,820
I'm going to sleep.

317
00:28:44,540 --> 00:28:45,860
If you’ve got something to say, say it.

318
00:28:46,610 --> 00:28:47,640
Your name’s Dao, right?

319
00:28:48,020 --> 00:28:48,670
Yes.

320
00:28:49,560 --> 00:28:51,300
I have something I want to ask for your help with.

321
00:28:52,540 --> 00:28:53,430
Help with what?

322
00:28:59,780 --> 00:29:00,990
I want Pad Kra Pao from Auntie Jum.

323
00:29:07,530 --> 00:29:10,540
Please. I really want to eat it.

324
00:29:11,470 --> 00:29:12,830
You yanked my leg—

325
00:29:13,530 --> 00:29:15,790
—just because you wanted Pad Kra Pao from Auntie Jum?

326
00:29:16,470 --> 00:29:17,100
No.

327
00:29:18,620 --> 00:29:19,380
There’s something else.

328
00:29:26,790 --> 00:29:27,650
What is it?

329
00:29:29,850 --> 00:29:30,980
Help me find out

330
00:29:31,850 --> 00:29:32,882
who killed me.

331
00:29:33,700 --> 00:29:35,080
Wasn’t it your girlfriend?

332
00:29:35,220 --> 00:29:36,710
The one who killed you?

333
00:29:36,810 --> 00:29:38,220
I don’t believe my girlfriend did it.

334
00:29:40,710 --> 00:29:43,140
Please. I’m begging you.

335
00:29:44,140 --> 00:29:45,060
No.

336
00:29:45,469 --> 00:29:46,400
I don’t want to get involved.

337
00:29:47,810 --> 00:29:49,240
Why are you so heartless?

338
00:29:49,450 --> 00:29:51,130
You look like such a nice person on the outside.

339
00:29:55,200 --> 00:29:56,310
Can’t you help me?

340
00:29:57,740 --> 00:29:59,360
Please, help me.

341
00:29:59,610 --> 00:30:00,400
Please?

342
00:30:03,230 --> 00:30:04,980
Otherwise, I’ll keep bothering you every night like this.

343
00:30:05,220 --> 00:30:06,560
Do you know that where you’re sleeping—

344
00:30:07,660 --> 00:30:08,630
—is right where I died?

345
00:30:10,376 --> 00:30:11,590
I can do anything to you.

346
00:30:12,770 --> 00:30:13,670
Are you threatening me?

347
00:30:26,110 --> 00:30:27,440
So how do you want me to help?

348
00:30:30,460 --> 00:30:31,040
I don’t know.

349
00:30:32,010 --> 00:30:32,540
What?

350
00:30:33,620 --> 00:30:35,310
Try asking the med student next door.

351
00:30:35,710 --> 00:30:36,860
He knows my girlfriend.

352
00:30:53,970 --> 00:30:55,720
Hey, are you done with class?

353
00:30:56,360 --> 00:30:57,730
I don’t have class today.

354
00:30:59,500 --> 00:31:00,240
Then what are you doing?

355
00:31:00,770 --> 00:31:01,570
Sleeping.

356
00:31:02,720 --> 00:31:05,130
Sleeping in the evening? A ghost might pin you down.

357
00:31:07,390 --> 00:31:08,300
What is it?

358
00:31:09,777 --> 00:31:11,880
I just finished class. I’ll come see you.

359
00:31:12,330 --> 00:31:13,490
Why?

360
00:31:14,613 --> 00:31:15,911
Okay, see you.

361
00:31:49,760 --> 00:31:50,940
Can you really stay here?

362
00:31:53,080 --> 00:31:54,090
Yeah, I can.

363
00:31:57,582 --> 00:31:59,994
I heard this place has…

364
00:32:03,750 --> 00:32:04,890
has…

365
00:32:07,190 --> 00:32:10,130
a pretty bad history.

366
00:32:11,960 --> 00:32:14,470
It might not be safe for you.

367
00:32:21,880 --> 00:32:24,770
Everyone’s just worried about you.

368
00:32:25,010 --> 00:32:26,540
Ter and Phoon are worried too.

369
00:32:27,500 --> 00:32:28,460
What about North?

370
00:32:29,430 --> 00:32:30,510
Me?

371
00:32:30,910 --> 00:32:32,140
Why would I be worried about you?

372
00:32:35,660 --> 00:32:37,290
You don’t need to worry about me.

373
00:32:37,660 --> 00:32:40,510
Once the condo owner found out about what happened here,

374
00:32:40,890 --> 00:32:43,420
they tightened up security a lot.

375
00:32:43,700 --> 00:32:44,930
The rent’s cheap.

376
00:32:45,550 --> 00:32:46,480
And besides,

377
00:32:46,750 --> 00:32:47,890
there aren’t many people.

378
00:32:48,110 --> 00:32:49,310
Just how I like it.

379
00:32:51,500 --> 00:32:55,340
Mm. If you can live with it, then it’s up to you.

380
00:32:58,810 --> 00:33:00,540
You haven’t run into anything weird, right?

381
00:33:02,850 --> 00:33:06,600
There’s still over 20 minutes before P’Jo picks me up. Want to play a game?

382
00:33:06,840 --> 00:33:08,420
Yeah, sure.

383
00:33:32,750 --> 00:33:34,530
Honestly, Dao,

384
00:33:34,820 --> 00:33:38,420
I saw you wanted to walk me to the front, so I let you.

385
00:33:38,630 --> 00:33:39,690
Actually,

386
00:33:39,760 --> 00:33:41,950
- I can go back by myself.
- Hey.

387
00:33:42,970 --> 00:33:43,980
Oh, P’Thit.

388
00:33:45,010 --> 00:33:45,720
What are you doing here?

389
00:33:46,270 --> 00:33:46,840
Well,

390
00:33:47,490 --> 00:33:49,610
my friend lives here, so I came to see him.

391
00:33:52,760 --> 00:33:54,290
What about you? What are you doing here?

392
00:33:54,760 --> 00:33:55,650
You live here?

393
00:33:57,050 --> 00:33:57,650
Yeah.

394
00:33:58,190 --> 00:33:59,150
Which room?

395
00:34:03,570 --> 00:34:04,260
Next door?

396
00:34:04,710 --> 00:34:05,280
Mm.

397
00:34:06,500 --> 00:34:07,990
Shit, what a coincidence.

398
00:34:08,980 --> 00:34:13,030
That makes me feel better. Leaving this guy alone is scary as hell.

399
00:34:14,190 --> 00:34:14,630
Hey.

400
00:34:15,870 --> 00:34:18,860
Or is having you next door even scarier?

401
00:34:21,390 --> 00:34:24,280
Hey, P'Thit.
You can just drop me off here.

402
00:34:24,480 --> 00:34:26,570
See you. P'Thit, let me see your room.

403
00:34:27,470 --> 00:34:28,970
Why are you following me, North?

404
00:34:29,090 --> 00:34:30,960
- Let me in.
- No need.

405
00:34:33,900 --> 00:34:34,830
Unbelievable.

406
00:34:35,560 --> 00:34:36,660
Why are you coming in?

407
00:34:39,690 --> 00:34:40,590
Take your shoes off too.

408
00:34:43,640 --> 00:34:44,690
Shit.

409
00:34:47,830 --> 00:34:49,180
So damn nice.

410
00:34:54,810 --> 00:34:55,460
Hey.

411
00:34:56,760 --> 00:34:58,070
This is freaking beautiful, P'.

412
00:34:58,500 --> 00:34:59,370
How much was this?

413
00:34:59,690 --> 00:35:01,890
Two or three hundred thousand, I think. I don’t remember.

414
00:35:02,060 --> 00:35:02,900
Does it bite?

415
00:35:03,410 --> 00:35:04,690
- Wanna try?
- No thanks.

416
00:35:04,890 --> 00:35:05,960
Don’t open it. No.

417
00:35:10,180 --> 00:35:13,470
You said you used to live alone on this whole floor, right?

418
00:35:14,040 --> 00:35:14,670
Really?

419
00:35:15,770 --> 00:35:16,510
Yeah.

420
00:35:17,230 --> 00:35:18,540
Now I’ve got your friend here.

421
00:35:20,600 --> 00:35:23,510
Since my friend moved in, please take care of him.

422
00:35:23,720 --> 00:35:24,890
Why’d he move here anyway?

423
00:35:25,150 --> 00:35:27,420
I thought I’d get to live alone until graduation.

424
00:35:27,790 --> 00:35:30,180
The owner gave that room a 70% discount.

425
00:35:30,270 --> 00:35:32,220
Huh? 70%?

426
00:35:33,000 --> 00:35:34,880
Yeah, so he moved in right away.

427
00:35:35,750 --> 00:35:37,350
I only got 50%, damn it.

428
00:35:39,400 --> 00:35:40,510
That’s more than me.

429
00:35:41,330 --> 00:35:41,740
Well...

430
00:35:43,050 --> 00:35:43,630
What’s with you?

431
00:35:44,400 --> 00:35:46,650
Someone died in that room.

432
00:35:46,830 --> 00:35:49,160
If you want a bigger discount, move in there instead.

433
00:35:49,220 --> 00:35:51,170
Hell no.

434
00:35:52,360 --> 00:35:53,240
Whatever.

435
00:35:54,730 --> 00:35:55,890
What’s wrong with you?

436
00:35:56,140 --> 00:35:57,030
It’s right next door.

437
00:36:00,810 --> 00:36:02,410
Come on, can you head back now?

438
00:36:02,940 --> 00:36:04,880
I’m exhausted. I’m going to sleep.

439
00:36:05,040 --> 00:36:06,100
Why are you chasing me away?

440
00:36:06,670 --> 00:36:07,440
Fine, I’ll go.

441
00:36:08,000 --> 00:36:08,580
Shit.

442
00:36:09,690 --> 00:36:11,140
Has P'Jo arrived yet?

443
00:36:11,930 --> 00:36:14,020
He should’ve. He left with me.

444
00:36:15,970 --> 00:36:16,470
Mm.

445
00:36:17,680 --> 00:36:18,300
Let’s go.

446
00:36:20,520 --> 00:36:22,330
- Walk me downstairs.
- Huh?

447
00:36:23,590 --> 00:36:25,630
Shit, North. You’re grown as hell already.

448
00:36:25,970 --> 00:36:28,660
You’re tall as a buffalo now. Go on, get out.

449
00:36:29,410 --> 00:36:30,450
Please, P'.

450
00:36:30,500 --> 00:36:31,530
Walk me down.

451
00:36:31,710 --> 00:36:32,730
Please.

452
00:36:35,460 --> 00:36:37,690
North looks cute in his engineer uniform today.

453
00:36:38,780 --> 00:36:40,840
You say he's cute every day.

454
00:36:41,420 --> 00:36:43,290
Is he close with the guy next door?

455
00:36:44,890 --> 00:36:46,630
He’s North boyfriend’s friend.

456
00:36:47,260 --> 00:36:50,090
North boyfriend’s handsome. They two suit each other.

457
00:36:51,760 --> 00:36:52,260
Mm.

458
00:36:58,060 --> 00:36:58,850
What’s wrong with you?

459
00:37:01,510 --> 00:37:04,250
You’re late. Couldn’t keep up with me?

460
00:37:05,270 --> 00:37:05,970
Shut up.

461
00:37:14,480 --> 00:37:15,870
Alright, see you.

462
00:37:16,380 --> 00:37:17,290
See you.

463
00:37:44,610 --> 00:37:45,710
What’s up?

464
00:37:46,570 --> 00:37:47,810
This is your dad.

465
00:37:48,130 --> 00:37:49,180
Watch your tone.

466
00:37:50,780 --> 00:37:51,570
Direk.

467
00:37:52,520 --> 00:37:53,650
Am I your buddy or what?

468
00:37:56,130 --> 00:37:57,310
Direk is my father.

469
00:37:59,520 --> 00:38:02,520
Or if you want to be friend, just say so.

470
00:38:03,670 --> 00:38:06,680
You little brat. If you weren’t my son—

471
00:38:07,900 --> 00:38:10,300
So what is it? Why’d you call?

472
00:38:10,430 --> 00:38:12,760
Hey, you haven’t gone to the racetrack lately?

473
00:38:13,690 --> 00:38:15,700
I’ve been busy as hell, Direk.

474
00:38:15,990 --> 00:38:19,500
Morning and evening shifts nonstop. I wanna quit, Direk.

475
00:38:20,360 --> 00:38:21,280
Support me, will you?

476
00:38:22,290 --> 00:38:24,530
What, I’m not supporting you already? Huh?

477
00:38:24,890 --> 00:38:27,530
Seriously, where else would you find a great dad like me?

478
00:38:27,630 --> 00:38:28,570
Oh please.

479
00:38:30,840 --> 00:38:32,740
And stop blocking me on LINE.

480
00:38:33,620 --> 00:38:34,730
I already unblocked you.

481
00:38:35,690 --> 00:38:37,580
You keep making Johan talk to me instead.

482
00:38:37,740 --> 00:38:40,880
Oh come on, Direk. You talk to Jo just fine.

483
00:38:41,370 --> 00:38:43,740
But your actual son, you won’t talk to.

484
00:38:44,020 --> 00:38:45,650
Johan’s cute.

485
00:38:45,810 --> 00:38:47,660
He actually makes sense.

486
00:38:47,840 --> 00:38:48,260
Oh?

487
00:38:50,180 --> 00:38:51,690
So I don’t make sense or what?

488
00:38:51,950 --> 00:38:53,070
You’re annoying.

489
00:38:53,190 --> 00:38:54,210
What's your problem?

490
00:38:55,000 --> 00:38:57,830
You only ever call to ask for money. You think I’m rich?

491
00:38:58,010 --> 00:39:01,160
If you’re not rich, just say so. I’ll borrow from Jo instead.

492
00:39:04,190 --> 00:39:04,810
So?

493
00:39:05,770 --> 00:39:06,460
What is it?

494
00:39:06,900 --> 00:39:07,900
Why’d you call?

495
00:39:10,780 --> 00:39:11,780
I had a bad dream.

496
00:39:12,040 --> 00:39:14,620
Shit, am I supposed to comfort you now?

497
00:39:14,770 --> 00:39:15,820
It’s okay, Dad.

498
00:39:15,930 --> 00:39:18,970
Your nightmare will turn into something good, okay?
Like that?

499
00:39:19,120 --> 00:39:21,990
Your dad, my ass.

500
00:39:22,620 --> 00:39:23,470
You’re cursing yourself again.

501
00:39:28,520 --> 00:39:30,200
Oh? And what did you dream about?

502
00:39:31,970 --> 00:39:33,180
I dreamed about your mom.

503
00:39:45,330 --> 00:39:46,130
Emma?

504
00:39:47,360 --> 00:39:47,930
Yeah.

505
00:39:54,860 --> 00:39:56,050
What did she say?

506
00:39:58,980 --> 00:40:00,360
She didn’t say anything.

507
00:40:00,840 --> 00:40:01,430
Same as always.

508
00:40:08,300 --> 00:40:10,190
You’re probably working too much, Direk.

509
00:40:10,780 --> 00:40:11,920
Get some rest.

510
00:40:14,060 --> 00:40:15,420
Yeah, I guess so.

511
00:40:22,720 --> 00:40:23,430
Mm.

512
00:41:03,850 --> 00:41:06,180
I’m gonna sleep like crazy tomorrow. It’s my day off.

513
00:41:07,740 --> 00:41:10,310
Jo, wanna go out for drinks tonight?

514
00:41:10,880 --> 00:41:12,420
Celebrate our one day off?

515
00:41:13,220 --> 00:41:15,640
Nah. I’d rather go home and cuddle my wife.

516
00:41:18,090 --> 00:41:19,580
For once, Jo said something nice.

517
00:41:20,650 --> 00:41:22,100
Yeah, seriously.

518
00:41:22,770 --> 00:41:24,120
Alright, let’s split up.

519
00:41:24,330 --> 00:41:25,440
Hope I never see you again.

520
00:41:26,730 --> 00:41:28,250
Yeah, get outta here.

521
00:41:28,520 --> 00:41:30,360
Go cuddle your wife, asshole.

522
00:41:30,400 --> 00:41:32,460
I’ll live the single life for you guys.

523
00:41:39,890 --> 00:41:41,920
Bottoms up.

524
00:41:42,071 --> 00:41:42,960
Another round.

525
00:41:45,708 --> 00:41:49,708
( Watch on www.kissasia.co, .club, .be, .org, .net, .id, .xyz )

526
00:41:47,733 --> 00:41:48,334
Let me.

527
00:41:52,157 --> 00:41:53,511
Finish your glass!

528
00:41:54,480 --> 00:41:56,910
Hey, the music’s great. Let’s go!

529
00:41:59,690 --> 00:42:01,310
Finish your drink first.

530
00:42:25,340 --> 00:42:26,640
Shit.

531
00:42:45,160 --> 00:42:47,610
Hey, open the door for me.

532
00:42:47,660 --> 00:42:49,170
Let me crash here.

533
00:42:51,350 --> 00:42:53,660
I lost my keycard.

534
00:42:54,160 --> 00:42:56,120
Open up.

535
00:43:02,710 --> 00:43:06,000
Can I crash on your couch?

536
00:43:10,222 --> 00:43:10,874
Thanks.

537
00:43:11,050 --> 00:43:13,440
Ugh, you asshole.

538
00:43:13,760 --> 00:43:16,190
Hey, I can sleep on the couch!

539
00:43:16,250 --> 00:43:17,620
So damn stingy.

540
00:43:31,530 --> 00:43:32,310
Hey.

541
00:43:33,750 --> 00:43:35,340
Open the door.

542
00:43:57,552 --> 00:44:00,583
He said he lost his keycard. Just help him out.

543
00:44:00,696 --> 00:44:02,580
If you leave him out there, the mosquitoes will carry him away.

544
00:44:16,320 --> 00:44:17,320
Hey.

545
00:44:17,900 --> 00:44:19,690
Let me stay over.

546
00:44:22,280 --> 00:44:24,380
Hey, next door!

547
00:44:42,330 --> 00:44:44,450
What the hell is this? Mosquito repellent?

548
00:44:46,420 --> 00:44:48,120
Well, that works too.

549
00:44:48,650 --> 00:44:49,690
So they won’t bite me.

550
00:44:50,500 --> 00:44:52,060
Ugh, asshole.

551
00:45:01,680 --> 00:45:02,670
North.

552
00:45:05,780 --> 00:45:08,000
What did you tell your friend?

553
00:45:08,960 --> 00:45:11,920
I told him not to leave you outside or the mosquitoes would carry you off.

554
00:45:13,282 --> 00:45:14,740
So? Did you get in?

555
00:45:14,770 --> 00:45:17,220
He gave me mosquito repellent instead.

556
00:45:27,550 --> 00:45:28,310
Hey.

557
00:45:30,150 --> 00:45:32,050
Can I use your bathroom?

558
00:45:32,690 --> 00:45:33,430
Hey.

559
00:45:34,590 --> 00:45:35,500
Hey.

560
00:45:37,880 --> 00:45:38,670
You.

561
00:45:40,060 --> 00:45:43,150
If you don’t let me in, I’m gonna puke in front of your door.

562
00:46:13,800 --> 00:46:16,150
What did I do to deserve this?

563
00:46:30,730 --> 00:46:32,130
Shut up.

564
00:46:36,680 --> 00:46:38,830
I said shut up.

565
00:46:41,420 --> 00:46:43,370
Won’t you bring him inside?

566
00:46:45,290 --> 00:46:46,050
No.

567
00:46:47,480 --> 00:46:48,360
Why?

568
00:46:51,690 --> 00:46:52,800
It’s a hassle.

569
00:46:53,690 --> 00:46:55,520
Why should I help him?

570
00:46:56,450 --> 00:46:58,230
Don’t be so heartless.

571
00:46:58,520 --> 00:46:59,680
You’re neighbors.

572
00:47:00,000 --> 00:47:03,880
In the future, Michael might need his help too.

573
00:47:22,150 --> 00:47:24,700
It’s so hard to fix that cold personality of yours.

574
00:47:36,660 --> 00:47:37,580
Thit.

575
00:47:40,000 --> 00:47:40,820
Hey, Thit.

576
00:47:41,150 --> 00:47:42,880
Arthit.

577
00:47:43,050 --> 00:47:45,690
Shit, I’m trying to sleep, asshole.

578
00:47:45,960 --> 00:47:48,890
Come on, talk to me.

579
00:47:50,360 --> 00:47:51,390
I’m serious.

580
00:47:51,670 --> 00:47:55,670
It takes a shit ton of energy for me to appear in your dream.

581
00:47:56,520 --> 00:47:58,180
This time, I’m serious.

582
00:48:04,930 --> 00:48:06,730
I want Aunt Jum’s Pad Kra Phao.

583
00:48:06,880 --> 00:48:08,360
Light some incense and bring it to me.

584
00:48:10,810 --> 00:48:14,430
Aunt Jum ran off with a younger guy to Surat.

585
00:48:18,270 --> 00:48:20,810
Then tell my mom I want Pad Kra Phao.

586
00:48:21,250 --> 00:48:22,580
Tell her to stop bringing me stew.

587
00:48:22,690 --> 00:48:23,850
I’m sick of stew.

588
00:48:29,820 --> 00:48:30,810
Seriously.

589
00:48:32,520 --> 00:48:34,460
I think the reason I haven’t been reborn yet

590
00:48:34,620 --> 00:48:35,850
is because I have unfinished business.

591
00:48:38,510 --> 00:48:39,550
I feel like

592
00:48:39,600 --> 00:48:40,560
Meen didn’t kill me.

593
00:49:58,730 --> 00:49:59,800
Time to wake up.

594
00:50:03,150 --> 00:50:04,300
Time to wake up.

595
00:50:11,500 --> 00:50:12,640
Is it morning already?

596
00:50:15,860 --> 00:50:17,550
Did I sleep here last night?

597
00:50:27,230 --> 00:50:27,770
Mm.

598
00:50:35,740 --> 00:50:36,700
What’s this?

599
00:50:36,860 --> 00:50:38,650
P’Pae left it for you this morning.

600
00:50:40,010 --> 00:50:41,480
He said don’t lose it again.

601
00:50:59,830 --> 00:51:01,790
Thanks for letting me crash here.

602
00:51:06,980 --> 00:51:07,820
Wait.

603
00:51:09,510 --> 00:51:10,220
What?

604
00:51:10,540 --> 00:51:11,330
Your shirt.

605
00:51:24,180 --> 00:51:25,370
Thanks.

606
00:51:50,420 --> 00:51:51,390
Seriously.

607
00:51:51,760 --> 00:51:55,420
I think the reason I haven’t been reborn yet is because I have unfinished business.

608
00:51:55,940 --> 00:51:58,190
I feel like Meen didn’t kill me.

609
00:52:13,825 --> 00:52:15,770
Hey, long time no see.

610
00:52:17,230 --> 00:52:17,750
Yeah.

611
00:52:19,620 --> 00:52:22,050
How’ve you been? You doing okay?

612
00:52:22,740 --> 00:52:23,800
That outfit looks good on you.

613
00:52:24,360 --> 00:52:25,970
Having fun, I guess. Asshole.

614
00:52:26,650 --> 00:52:28,840
The hell kinda question is that? I’m in prison.

615
00:52:33,370 --> 00:52:34,390
What the hell are you doing here?

616
00:52:34,790 --> 00:52:36,100
- Visiting?
- Yeah.

617
00:52:36,620 --> 00:52:39,230
Yeah, visiting you. I just talked to Do last night.

618
00:52:39,450 --> 00:52:40,760
How many hits did you take?

619
00:52:41,120 --> 00:52:42,720
Taking hits my ass.

620
00:52:43,400 --> 00:52:45,170
That bastard Do keeps showing up in my dreams.

621
00:52:46,220 --> 00:52:50,810
Ever since he died, he’s been coming over to my room all the damn time.

622
00:52:51,310 --> 00:52:53,140
It’s fucking annoying as hell.

623
00:52:53,850 --> 00:52:55,530
What’s his problem? Lonely or what?

624
00:52:56,110 --> 00:52:56,750
Damn it.

625
00:53:02,140 --> 00:53:03,020
Hey, Meen.

626
00:53:04,130 --> 00:53:04,890
Your old room—

627
00:53:05,950 --> 00:53:07,280
someone’s already moved in.

628
00:53:08,310 --> 00:53:09,160
Seriously?

629
00:53:09,630 --> 00:53:10,260
Yeah.

630
00:53:13,260 --> 00:53:16,670
What kind of idiot would live in a room that haunted?

631
00:53:16,960 --> 00:53:18,220
More crowded than mosquitoes.

632
00:53:19,450 --> 00:53:20,090
Mm.

633
00:53:22,240 --> 00:53:23,530
Someone who can talk to spirits.

634
00:53:23,720 --> 00:53:24,430
Funny.

635
00:53:24,610 --> 00:53:27,130
Yeah, fucking hilarious.

636
00:53:27,660 --> 00:53:29,590
Who the hell can even talk to ghosts?

637
00:53:30,840 --> 00:53:31,740
You can.

638
00:53:32,030 --> 00:53:33,580
You’re still talking to Do.

639
00:53:33,980 --> 00:53:34,910
And you’re mocking others.

640
00:53:35,470 --> 00:53:37,400
You used to live in that room too.

641
00:53:38,030 --> 00:53:38,540
Damn it.

642
00:53:39,430 --> 00:53:40,940
The rent was cheap.

643
00:53:41,790 --> 00:53:42,780
Besides,

644
00:53:43,770 --> 00:53:44,950
I’m not afraid of ghosts.

645
00:53:46,740 --> 00:53:50,150
You know, I was close with the ghosts in that room.

646
00:53:51,700 --> 00:53:55,800
Only that idiot Do was scared shitless.

647
00:54:02,580 --> 00:54:03,310
Hey.

648
00:54:04,310 --> 00:54:05,540
Has he visited you?

649
00:54:07,520 --> 00:54:10,010
A ghost that’s scared of ghosts, maybe.

650
00:54:10,200 --> 00:54:15,090
Can you believe it? He told me he’s being bullied by a female ghost in the room.

651
00:54:15,370 --> 00:54:17,890
It’s fucking pathetic, Meen.

652
00:54:18,620 --> 00:54:20,740
Without me, no one can protect him.

653
00:54:35,280 --> 00:54:35,950
Meen.

654
00:54:36,690 --> 00:54:37,040
Hm?

655
00:54:39,550 --> 00:54:41,240
Do said you didn’t kill him.

656
00:54:49,730 --> 00:54:51,100
I’ll be honest with you, Mhor.

657
00:54:53,410 --> 00:54:55,270
- I don’t know.
- What?

658
00:54:57,170 --> 00:54:58,360
What do you mean you don’t know?

659
00:54:59,590 --> 00:55:02,680
Back then, we were fighting like crazy.

660
00:55:02,860 --> 00:55:04,410
How could you cheat on me?

661
00:55:04,560 --> 00:55:06,810
I told you I didn’t. Look at this.

662
00:55:06,930 --> 00:55:09,730
Don’t lie to me. You think I’m an idiot?

663
00:55:11,320 --> 00:55:12,920
Hey, where are you going?

664
00:55:13,290 --> 00:55:17,390
Sometimes I even thought about killing him.

665
00:55:20,690 --> 00:55:21,710
And that night…

666
00:55:22,990 --> 00:55:25,500
I was wasted. I don’t remember a damn thing.

667
00:55:27,290 --> 00:55:30,090
When I woke up, he was lying in a pool of blood next to me.

668
00:55:31,420 --> 00:55:32,710
And I was holding a knife.

669
00:55:34,440 --> 00:55:35,820
If it wasn’t me, then who?

670
00:55:35,950 --> 00:55:36,600
Huh?

671
00:55:38,120 --> 00:55:38,690
Do.

672
00:55:42,430 --> 00:55:45,080
So you just assumed you killed him.

673
00:55:45,400 --> 00:55:46,790
If not me, then who?

674
00:55:47,500 --> 00:55:48,710
With evidence like that.

675
00:55:51,590 --> 00:55:54,330
But that idiot swears you didn’t kill him.

676
00:55:54,740 --> 00:55:57,220
Problem is, he can’t remember that night either.

677
00:55:58,300 --> 00:56:00,120
Then who the hell would want him dead?

678
00:56:00,940 --> 00:56:02,940
As far as I know, he didn’t have any enemies.

679
00:56:06,120 --> 00:56:06,850
Shit, Meen.

680
00:56:08,020 --> 00:56:09,470
What if someone else did it

681
00:56:10,160 --> 00:56:11,030
and you don’t know?

682
00:56:15,720 --> 00:56:18,410
That night, the CCTV just happened to be broken.

683
00:56:19,450 --> 00:56:21,640
Who do you think saw what happened besides…

684
00:56:23,230 --> 00:56:24,540
Shit.

685
00:56:25,150 --> 00:56:26,330
The ghost in the room.

686
00:56:30,980 --> 00:56:31,930
Help me out.

687
00:56:32,470 --> 00:56:33,930
Can you talk to the ghost in that room for me?

688
00:56:35,980 --> 00:56:36,520
Please?

689
00:56:37,040 --> 00:56:37,500
No.

690
00:56:39,150 --> 00:56:40,140
Hey, wait.

691
00:56:57,020 --> 00:56:57,940
North.

692
00:56:59,240 --> 00:57:02,290
Your friend is such a pain in the ass.

693
00:57:09,063 --> 00:57:10,423
You really don’t remember anything from that night?

694
00:57:11,268 --> 00:57:14,355
Nothing. I didn’t even realize I was dead until days later.

695
00:57:14,450 --> 00:57:16,705
Then why not ask the other ghost in the room?

696
00:57:16,794 --> 00:57:17,937
P’Praw.

697
00:57:20,808 --> 00:57:24,918
The night Donut was killed, did you see anything, P’Cream?

698
00:57:26,548 --> 00:57:27,857
So you’re gonna help me, right?

699
00:57:30,420 --> 00:57:34,503
Before it happened, a woman went into your room and argued with Do.
